A CHORUS LINE

01:41.100 --> 01:46.413
Again!
Step, push, step, step, touch, kick.

01:49.860 --> 01:52.374
Good.

02:12.180 --> 02:16.970
The last part is:
Pivot, step, walk, walk, walk.

02:23.460 --> 02:28.329
The girl in white, the girl in blue,
boy in the green, Michele...

02:28.540 --> 02:32.499
Greg, the boy in the headband,
Diana, yellow sweats, and the pink.

02:32.700 --> 02:36.659
The rest, thank you very much.
Next group.

03:10.940 --> 03:15.536
Connie, girl with the red headband,
the girl in gray...

03:15.740 --> 03:19.050
The rest, thank you. Next group.

03:26.780 --> 03:30.250
- What’s he looking for?
- Baryshnikov.

03:32.420 --> 03:35.457
You’re going to be terrific.

03:50.900 --> 03:56.020
Gentlemen, get ready. The girl in
pink, Sheila. The rest, thank you.

03:56.220 --> 03:58.336
First group of guys.

04:38.540 --> 04:41.213
Grateful body, huh?

04:58.100 --> 05:00.056
Come on...

05:04.140 --> 05:07.815
This is all wrong.
Everybody back.

05:08.020 --> 05:11.569
You in the green.
You, honey, come on.

05:14.500 --> 05:18.209
Watch. This is right.
Five, six, seven, eight...

05:40.140 --> 05:44.736
See what I’m saying?
Just like that.

05:57.460 --> 06:02.409
Al, girl in the green,
boy in blue at the back.

06:02.620 --> 06:04.611
The rest, thank you.

06:07.140 --> 06:10.416
I’ve never been cut this soon.

06:10.620 --> 06:13.692
Zach! That’s all.

06:15.620 --> 06:20.819
Everybody on stage
The whole combination from the top.

06:29.740 --> 06:32.459
I want it strong.

06:32.660 --> 06:36.050
Make it sharp.
Ready? Five, six, seven, eight...

08:41.419 --> 08:43.570
Larry...

08:46.780 --> 08:48.930
You were great.

08:59.420 --> 09:03.208
<i>- Does that stuff work?
- It’s better than nothing.</i>

09:11.500 --> 09:13.695
Clear the stage!

09:13.900 --> 09:17.495
I"II put you into groups.
Listen for your number.

09:17.700 --> 09:20.214
First group: Stage right...

09:20.420 --> 09:24.572
- I forgot my number.
- So a number with no name is you.

09:28.100 --> 09:31.410
Right... 12, 19...

09:31.620 --> 09:36.489
228. 131. 32.

09:36.900 --> 09:41.690
46. 41. 29...

09:46.700 --> 09:49.817
<i>God, I hope I get it</i>

09:50.020 --> 09:52.773
<i>How many people does he need?</i>

09:52.980 --> 09:55.574
<i>I hope I get it</i>

09:55.780 --> 09:58.897
<i>How many boys,
how many girls?</i>

09:59.100 --> 10:03.013
101... 23.

10:03.220 --> 10:05.734
23?

10:06.100 --> 10:09.854
- Judy Monroe!
- 23.

10:10.300 --> 10:13.417
5... 25

10:20.860 --> 10:24.375
<i>Look at all the people!</i>

10:24.580 --> 10:29.370
<i>How many people does he need?
How many boys, how many girls?</i>

10:29.580 --> 10:34.654
<i>I really need this job
Please God, I need this job</i>

10:34.860 --> 10:39.650
<i>I’ve got to get this job</i>

10:39.860 --> 10:43.819
First group, ballet combination.

10:44.020 --> 10:46.659
Second group, be ready.

10:57.900 --> 11:02.610
- Morales, your tongue is out.
- Oh, shit!

11:02.820 --> 11:05.209
Next group!

11:23.340 --> 11:25.854
The girl in the yellow trunks.

11:26.060 --> 11:29.257
- Me?
- Yes. Do you know ballet?

11:29.460 --> 11:32.452
- No.
- Don’t dance.

11:34.340 --> 11:36.729
Don’t dance!

11:51.580 --> 11:53.730
Let’s go.

11:58.300 --> 12:01.770
God got out
the wrong side of the bed.

12:01.980 --> 12:07.100
I hate his auditions.
We’re being treated like worms.

12:07.300 --> 12:12.010
He’s a shit,
but goddamned talented.

12:18.300 --> 12:21.770
The boy in the headband, head up!

12:23.700 --> 12:26.453
Headband, head up!

12:26.660 --> 12:30.573
How long will he keep us?
My job starts at four.

12:30.780 --> 12:32.896
Call in sick.

12:33.100 --> 12:34.658
Make em sharp!

12:41.940 --> 12:44.977
<i>God, I really blew it</i>

12:45.180 --> 12:47.853
<i>How could I do a thing like that?</i>

12:48.060 --> 12:50.620
<i>Now I"II never make it</i>

12:50.820 --> 12:53.015
<i>He doesn’t like my looks</i>

12:53.220 --> 12:55.131
<i>He doesn’t like the way I dance</i>

12:55.740 --> 13:00.177
The blonde in the front:
Much better, but still too tense.

13:32.820 --> 13:38.258
I know there’s an audition,
but can I see the director?

13:38.460 --> 13:41.054
Leave him a note.

14:13.620 --> 14:16.851
Next group of girls.

14:18.540 --> 14:25.332
I hope you were listening, I don’t
want to say the same thing twice...

14:51.180 --> 14:56.777
Hold it! Sheila, dance upstage.
You in the peach, downstage.

15:10.460 --> 15:13.133
Next group of guys.

15:14.500 --> 15:19.893
- Don’t you know the combination?
- I knew it when I was in front.

15:20.100 --> 15:22.455
Get rid of the chewing gum!

15:23.260 --> 15:27.651
- I"II pick it up in 15 minutes.
- Can you get this to the director?

15:27.860 --> 15:32.934
I’m his secretary.
Sam, a messenger will pick this up.

15:33.140 --> 15:39.613
Give this to Zach and say
that Cassie wants to see him.

15:39.820 --> 15:43.574
Cassie?
Didn’t you use to be a dancer?

15:43.780 --> 15:47.614
I saw you here.
You stopped the show.

15:47.820 --> 15:50.732
I was in highschool.

15:50.940 --> 15:56.014
I’m sorry,
I didn’t mean to say it that way.

15:56.220 --> 16:00.259
- I"II get this to Zach right away.
- Thanks.

16:20.380 --> 16:23.292
My God, I don’t believe it.

16:23.500 --> 16:27.095
Did anybody know you were coming?

16:27.300 --> 16:30.531
No, I just came from the airport.

16:35.860 --> 16:39.296
Zach... Look who’s here.

16:52.500 --> 16:54.218
Hi, Cassie.

16:55.540 --> 17:00.614
- Sorry to bust in on you like this.
- No, it’s good to see you.

17:00.820 --> 17:03.015
We’re running late.

17:03.220 --> 17:08.089
- It’s important that I see you.
- Leave your number with Larry.

17:14.099 --> 17:20.096
- Hang on till the first break...
- Larry, let’s go.

17:57.420 --> 18:00.378
The last group of guys.

18:26.980 --> 18:30.609
Fine... just bring it down a bit.

19:11.540 --> 19:15.135
You came down a little hard
on Cassie.

19:16.340 --> 19:18.729
Thanks, Kim.

19:18.940 --> 19:24.651
We’re eliminating. When Larry calls
your number, please stand in line.

19:24.860 --> 19:29.650
Girls first. 14. 19...

19:31.980 --> 19:37.259
12...
364...

19:39.580 --> 19:42.492
23.

20:00.180 --> 20:04.014
The other girls,
thank you very much.

20:09.420 --> 20:11.376
Come on.

20:11.580 --> 20:17.450
Now boys...
18. 45. 44.

20:19.580 --> 20:22.811
- 17.
- That’s me.

20:33.580 --> 20:36.014
Excuse me.

20:40.820 --> 20:44.415
The rest of the guys, thanks a lot.

20:55.180 --> 20:58.377
<i>God, I really got it</i>

20:58.580 --> 21:01.140
<i>I knew he liked me</i>

21:01.340 --> 21:03.808
<i>I knew he liked me</i>

21:04.020 --> 21:06.818
We’ve got a lot to do
before the next elimination.

21:07.020 --> 21:11.616
Give your pictures
and resumés to Larry. Thank you.

21:11.820 --> 21:14.732
<i>What’s coming next?</i>

21:14.940 --> 21:17.773
<i>What’s coming now?</i>

21:17.980 --> 21:20.494
<i>God, I hope I get it</i>

21:20.700 --> 21:25.091
<i>I’ve come this far,
but it could be yes or no</i>

21:27.020 --> 21:29.898
<i>My unemployment is gone</i>

21:30.100 --> 21:32.568
<i>I thought I had it from the start</i>

21:32.780 --> 21:39.731
<i>I’ve got to get this show!</i>

21:52.540 --> 21:55.259
Larry, would you collect them?

21:55.460 --> 21:58.258
Kim, pick them up, please.

22:15.500 --> 22:18.890
<i>Who am I anyway?</i>

22:19.100 --> 22:22.775
<i>Am I my resumé?</i>

22:22.980 --> 22:29.658
<i>That is a picture
of a person I don’t know</i>

22:29.860 --> 22:32.977
<i>What does he want from me?</i>

22:33.180 --> 22:35.853
<i>What should I try to be?</i>

22:36.060 --> 22:41.088
<i>So many faces all around
and here we go</i>

22:41.300 --> 22:44.292
<i>I need this job</i>

22:45.780 --> 22:53.368
<i>Oh, God, I need this show.</i>

22:55.300 --> 22:57.814
Zach...

23:00.860 --> 23:04.694
- We’re running late, Cassie.
- I’m here to audition.

23:04.900 --> 23:09.815
- There’s nothing but the chorus.
- Okay, fine.

23:10.020 --> 23:14.616
Cassie, come on.
Okay, Larry, line them up.

23:14.820 --> 23:20.452
Tell me your name, stage name,
where you were born, your age.

23:20.660 --> 23:22.616
Cassie...

23:26.420 --> 23:29.571
First, please.

23:31.260 --> 23:37.096
Cass...
What’s all this about the chorus?

23:37.300 --> 23:41.771
- Is Tina Mason still on 85th?
- I haven’t seen her for years.

23:41.980 --> 23:46.610
I’d like to make a call
to Los Angeles 213-555-8535.

23:46.820 --> 23:53.055
- Larry, come here a minute!
- No, 213-555-8535... 7298.

23:57.780 --> 24:02.774
Maggie Winslow, sometimes known as
Margaret, Margie. Peggy.

24:02.980 --> 24:10.170
I was born in San Mateo, California,
on Thursday, August 17th, 1965.

24:10.380 --> 24:12.814
Mike Cass, but not always.

24:13.020 --> 24:16.376
I was Timothy Michael
Cassiday O'Donoghue.

24:16.580 --> 24:20.095
Trenton, New Jersey,
July 9th, 1960.

24:20.300 --> 24:24.498
Connie Wong,
always Wong, never right.

24:24.700 --> 24:29.820
Bad joke... Born in Chinatown,
Lower East Side.

24:30.020 --> 24:32.773
How old are you?

24:32.980 --> 24:38.612
I was born December 5th,
4642, the Year of the Chicken.

24:40.580 --> 24:44.414
My real name is
Sidney Kenneth Beckenstein.

24:44.620 --> 24:50.217
My Jewish name is Rochmel Lev Ben
Yokov Meyer Beckenstein.

24:50.420 --> 24:55.130
My professional name
is Gregory Gardner.

24:55.340 --> 25:02.018
Very East Side.
I happen to be a mere 28 years old.

25:06.820 --> 25:10.529
Sheila Bryant,
born in Colorado Springs, -

25:10.740 --> 25:15.530
- but I’ve always felt
more like Park Avenue.

25:15.740 --> 25:23.010
I’m going to be 30 real soon,
and I’m real glad.

25:25.140 --> 25:27.779
You want to rent for three months?

25:27.980 --> 25:32.895
I’m Robert Charles Joseph Mills III.
That’s my real name, too.

25:33.100 --> 25:38.572
I come from upstate New York,
I blocked the name of the town out.

25:38.780 --> 25:40.577
Age?

25:40.780 --> 25:43.772
- Tell him, Bobby.
- Why lie?

25:43.980 --> 25:47.529
Age is a state of mind.
What age do you want me to be?

25:47.740 --> 25:51.289
- Bobby, how old are you?
- 25...

25:55.820 --> 26:00.098
- Louder, please.
- My name is Bebe Benson.

26:00.300 --> 26:05.977
Beatrice Ann Benson,
Washington D.C. I’m 19 years old.

26:09.380 --> 26:14.170
My name is Judy Monroe,
but my real name is Marilyn Monroe.

26:16.900 --> 26:24.250
No... It’s always been Judy Monroe.
I’m 22, and I’m from El Paso.

26:24.460 --> 26:27.293
El Paso, Texas...

26:27.500 --> 26:30.572
Hi, my name is Richie Walters.

26:30.780 --> 26:34.455
21 years old, I was born
on a full moon in Missouri.

26:34.660 --> 26:37.413
And I’m black.

26:42.620 --> 26:47.250
Alan Deluca, 28 years old,
from the Bronx.

26:52.580 --> 26:57.335
I’m Kristine Erlich.
Kristine Evelyn Erlich.

26:57.540 --> 27:01.374
I’m eighteen years old...
last September.

27:01.580 --> 27:07.496
- Tell him where you’re from.
- I’m from St. Louis, Missouri.

27:07.700 --> 27:11.613
My married name is Deluca.

27:13.140 --> 27:15.700
Congratulations, Al.

27:21.140 --> 27:24.371
I call myself Valerie Clark.

27:24.580 --> 27:30.894
My parents think I’m Margaret Mary
Houlihan. Couldn’t you just die?

27:31.100 --> 27:36.458
I was born in the middle of nowhere
near Arlington, Vermont.

27:36.660 --> 27:38.935
Age?

27:39.140 --> 27:44.260
Old.
24... and a half.

27:46.660 --> 27:50.699
Mark Anthony...
I think is going to be my stage name.

27:50.900 --> 27:54.734
I’m really Mark Philip Tabori
from Tempe, Arizona.

27:54.940 --> 28:00.333
I’m 17 years old, and if I get
this show, I"II work real hard.

28:02.780 --> 28:07.854
Paul San Marco is my stage name.
My real name is Ephrain Ramirez...

28:08.060 --> 28:09.971
Could you hold it a minute?

28:16.820 --> 28:22.770
- Sorry. Paul, was it?
- Paul San Marco’s my stage name.

28:22.980 --> 28:27.929
My real name is Ephrain Ramirez,
born in Spanish Harlem, age 22.

28:31.220 --> 28:35.338
Diana Morales. I didn’t change it
because I thought ethnic was in.

28:35.540 --> 28:39.453
Born 10-4-"62 on a
Hollywood bed in the Bronx.

28:43.140 --> 28:46.371
Go on, Diana.

28:47.780 --> 28:52.296
Go on what? I gave you my picture
with my resumé.

28:52.500 --> 28:58.211
Tell me what’s not on it.
Tell me about the Bronx.

28:58.420 --> 29:02.572
What’s to tell?
It’s uptown and to the right.

29:04.380 --> 29:07.577
- What made you start dancing?
- Who knows?

29:07.780 --> 29:10.817
Puerto Ricans jump around a lot.

29:15.660 --> 29:20.688
If you want to know if I can act,
give me a scene. I"II act.

29:20.900 --> 29:24.336
But I can't just talk.

29:26.140 --> 29:30.179
- Please, I’m too nervous.
- You want the job, don’t you?

29:32.060 --> 29:34.290
Of course.

29:36.260 --> 29:38.376
Back in line.

29:42.380 --> 29:45.292
Before we do any more dancing, -

29:45.500 --> 29:50.654
- let me explain that this
will not be like other auditions.

29:50.860 --> 29:55.012
I’m looking for a strong chorus,
people who can work together.

29:55.220 --> 30:01.056
I’m going to try to shake you up,
see who you really are.

30:01.260 --> 30:07.779
We’ve got some small but important
parts for people in the chorus.

30:07.980 --> 30:13.100
I need great dancers, so I can’t
expect you all to be great actors.

30:13.300 --> 30:20.297
So I don’t want anybody
to try to act. Understand?

30:20.500 --> 30:26.530
Just be who you are. That’s just
as important as how you dance.

30:26.740 --> 30:33.179
I’m going to ask you some questions.
I want to know details about you.

30:33.380 --> 30:37.612
Things you’re proud of,
things you’re ashamed of.

30:37.820 --> 30:41.972
If anybody can’t handle it
and wants to leave, -

30:42.180 --> 30:45.058
- now is the time.

31:01.740 --> 31:05.813
Honey...
Could we please go?

31:06.020 --> 31:08.534
We’re going to be fine.

31:12.300 --> 31:18.216
<i>We’re Puerto Ricans. To them,
we’re ashamed of everything.</i>

31:21.540 --> 31:26.455
If I could think of anything I’d be
ashamed of, I’d have tried it.

31:26.660 --> 31:31.051
Look, Zach...
I just need a minute.

31:37.180 --> 31:40.217
- How many jobs are there?
- Four and four.

31:40.420 --> 31:43.014
44?

31:43.220 --> 31:47.133
- Four boys, four girls.
- Any women?

31:54.100 --> 31:58.013
Dick,
I’m going to need a spotlight.

32:01.060 --> 32:04.939
Zach said he'll call you
as soon as he can.

32:05.140 --> 32:09.895
And he told me to ask you
in a nice way...

32:12.100 --> 32:15.172
...would you mind leaving?

32:26.860 --> 32:29.055
Shit!

32:31.820 --> 32:34.812
- Taxi!
- Cassie!

32:39.380 --> 32:41.735
Are you all right?

32:41.940 --> 32:45.410
- Are you okay?
- I’m fine.

32:56.020 --> 33:01.811
- Okay, Michael. You start.
- Me? Why not start at the end?

33:02.020 --> 33:06.059
- What would you like to tell me?
- To start at the end.

33:06.260 --> 33:12.051
- Wait in the musicians" room.
- He told me to leave.

33:12.260 --> 33:16.412
- Shut up. Are you all right?
- Fine.

33:16.620 --> 33:20.295
- I"II get some ice for your elbow.
- I feel terrible.

33:20.500 --> 33:26.132
- What made you start dancing?
- My sister. She was a girl.

33:26.340 --> 33:31.972
So she got all the dancing lessons.
Once in a while she took me along.

33:32.180 --> 33:36.332
- How old were you?
- Four. I’d sit there and...

33:36.540 --> 33:39.213
<i>I’m watching sis go pitapat</i>

33:39.420 --> 33:43.857
<i>I said, "I can do that"
"I can do that"</i>

33:44.060 --> 33:47.211
<i>Knew every step right off the bat</i>

33:47.420 --> 33:51.936
<i>I can do that
I can do that</i>

33:52.140 --> 33:56.019
<i>One morning sis won’t go
to dance class</i>

33:56.220 --> 34:00.133
<i>I grabbed her shoes, tights and all
but my foot’s too small</i>

34:00.340 --> 34:03.298
<i>I stuffed her shoes
with extra socks</i>

34:03.500 --> 34:07.209
<i>Ran seven blocks in nothing flat</i>

34:07.420 --> 34:11.572
<i>I can do that
That I can do</i>

34:14.219 --> 34:16.415
Give me some room!

35:58.660 --> 36:03.814
<i>All thanks to sis,
I can do that.</i>

36:12.260 --> 36:15.855
Have you got any ice
for my ego?

36:16.060 --> 36:19.291
You know what Zach’s like
when he’s working...

36:19.500 --> 36:23.493
What are you talking to me
like I’m a grown-up for?

36:23.700 --> 36:28.330
Just stay put,
and keep that ice on your elbow.

36:28.540 --> 36:33.011
- Does Zach still think I...
- Let’s get one thing straight.

36:33.220 --> 36:39.136
You can stay with me, but I’m not
getting between you and Zach.

36:48.140 --> 36:51.098
I don’t know how I turned out
this heavenly.

36:51.300 --> 36:55.532
- Are you going to do a routine?
- No, moving right along.

36:55.740 --> 36:58.618
Start with your family.

36:58.820 --> 37:03.177
Do you want to know the wonderful
things, or do you want the truth?

37:03.380 --> 37:06.531
I"II take the truth.

37:06.740 --> 37:13.054
My mother was one of the foremost
bridge cheaters in America.

37:13.260 --> 37:19.017
My father worked for a big
corporation. He was away a lot...

37:19.220 --> 37:22.769
...to drink.
But they were okay.

37:22.980 --> 37:26.450
- I was the strange one.
- How strange?

37:26.660 --> 37:29.891
Real, real strange.

37:31.420 --> 37:34.218
Bizarre.

37:34.420 --> 37:38.493
As I got older,
I got stranger and stranger.

37:38.700 --> 37:41.055
I started breaking in.

37:41.260 --> 37:44.491
I didn’t steal anything,
I just rearranged.

37:45.740 --> 37:51.929
I went to an expensive private
school for the exceptionally stupid.

37:52.140 --> 37:56.850
Jock City. I always got slammed
into lockers.

37:57.060 --> 38:01.099
Not only by the students,
by the teachers, too.

38:01.300 --> 38:07.216
I couldn’t catch a ball. And my father
was a big ex-football hero.

38:07.420 --> 38:13.939
He was so humiliated
that he told his friends I had polio.

38:14.140 --> 38:18.611
On Father’s Day
I used to limp for him.

38:18.820 --> 38:24.258
And I was always thinking up
spectacular ways of killing myself.

38:24.460 --> 38:29.659
But I realized, to commit suicide
in Buffalo is redundant.

38:29.860 --> 38:35.492
- Exactly what you don’t want, right?
- Exactly.

38:35.700 --> 38:37.179
Dick! Give me the spotlight.

38:42.300 --> 38:45.815
To the left. A little more. Hold it.

38:46.020 --> 38:48.011
Sheila.

38:50.380 --> 38:52.894
Is there anything you want to tell me?

38:53.100 --> 38:57.378
What do I want to be
when I grow up?

38:57.580 --> 39:02.734
Young.
Don’t you have any softer light?

39:02.940 --> 39:06.012
Come closer.

39:06.220 --> 39:11.214
- Can I sit on your lap?
- Do you always come on like this?

39:11.420 --> 39:15.459
No. Sometimes I’m aggressive.

39:15.660 --> 39:20.973
- Tell me about your parents.
- My parents?

39:21.180 --> 39:24.217
About your mother.

